### 2.3 Business Model

Burger Empire operates a **delivery-first QSR model** with limited dine-in capacity. The strategy: multiple micro-outlets (200–500 sq ft kitchens) embedded in high-density residential and educational zones — maximizing delivery radius coverage across Gwalior without centralized mall anchors. The FOFO franchise model enables capital-efficient geographic expansion. SOPs, supply chain logistics, and training matrices are deployed to ensure product consistency across franchise nodes.

**Kitchen model:** Pre-processed frozen primary ingredients (patties, fries) + rapid-assembly proprietary sauces. Minimizes skilled labor requirement, reduces friction, ensures consistency.

