### 3.5 Competitive Gaps & Opportunities

**Where BB has advantage:**
- Only multi-outlet local chain with city-wide delivery coverage
- Stronger cultural familiarity and localized menu (Veg Makhani, Desi Masala Crunch, Paneer Supreme) vs global chains
- Established 35,401-order customer base with repeat buyers

**Where BB is losing ground:**
- Veg/non-veg trust deficit post legal verdict — national chains exploit this
- No app, no loyalty programme — BK's Rs.99 app combos directly poach BB's core student segment
- Rating gap: BB 4.1–4.3 vs BK 4.6 — meaningful in aggregator search algorithms

**Unexploited opportunities:**
- Late-night delivery (11pm–2am) underserved by national chains; could add 20–30% revenue
- KFC quality inconsistency noted in reviews — BB can capture dissatisfied KFC users with superior veg options
- Gwalior-specific flavor IP that national chains cannot replicate (regional masala profiles)

