### 4.3 Three Critical Turning Points

**Turning Point #1 — April 2025 (First Warning — Swiggy)**
- Swiggy collapsed: 239 (Feb) → 121 (Apr) = **-49.4% in 2 months**
- Canary in the coal mine — 8+ months before Zomato collapse
- Likely triggered by Swiggy algorithm demotion following legal case complaint filing (Feb 2024)

**Turning Point #2 — November 2025 (Second Warning — Full Deceleration)**
- Total orders: 3,441 (Oct) → 2,554 (Nov) = **-25.8% in one month**
- Swiggy hit 117 (Nov) then 61 (Dec) — effectively zero; platform fully demoted
- Net sales: Rs.8.77L → Rs.5.61L in Oct–Dec = **-35.9% in 2 months**
- Highest-ever discounts (Rs.1.26L in Oct) failed to defend volume

**Turning Point #3 — February 2026 (Full Crisis)**
- Zomato: 551 (Feb '25) → 154 (Feb '26) = **-72.1% YoY** — catastrophic platform collapse
- Swiggy: 239 (Feb '25) → 94 (Feb '26) = **-60.7% YoY**
- AOV paradoxically rose to Rs.280 (highest ever): remaining customers are high-value but volume has imploded
- Daily avg: 55.2 orders/day vs annual 2025 avg of 97.0/day

