**Zomato Platform Algorithm Demotion + Commission Squeeze**

Two simultaneous platform dynamics:

**Root Cause Chain:**
- Level 1: Legal verdict triggered Zomato to deprioritize BB listings + threaten dismissal
- Level 2: Simultaneous commission inflation (16–35% per order) makes BB's net revenue Rs.160–200 on a Rs.245 order
- Level 3: Platform fee hike 20% (Rs.5 to Rs.6, April 2025) + paid priority listings favor national chains

**Platform factor breakdown:**

| Platform Factor | Impact on Burger Empire |
|---|---|
| Zomato "dismissal threat" post legal verdict | Likely de-ranked in search — fewer organic orders |
| Commission 16–35% per order | BB nets only Rs.160–200 on Rs.245 AOV after platform fee |
| Platform fee hiked 20% (April 2025) | Customers pay more; BB less competitive vs dine-in |
| Paid priority listings | National chains (BK, McD, KFC) outbid BB for top placement |
| Algorithm downward spiral | Fewer orders → lower ranking → even fewer orders |
| Rapido enters food delivery at 8–15% commission | New competitor squeezing aggregators, creating market uncertainty |

**Evidence:** Zomato Feb 2026: 154 orders vs 551 in Feb 2025 = -72.1% — far beyond normal seasonality.

